summary: What do you think of Pokemon Sword & Shield? I don't like it, it looks like they're trying to play it safe again and follow the...
question: What do you think of Pokemon Sword & Shield? I don't like it, it looks like they're trying to play it safe again and follow the same old tired formula. You know, newbie trainer, three starters, collecting badges, etc. Why? This game they'll get to have the game on a much more powerful game console so why does the game look like something from the 3DS. Why not do something new? The starters are okay, the only one I thought looked nice was the fire rabbit.
answer:
I agree, it looks pretty tame and uninteresting, it’s the same thing over and over again, 0 ambititon and thanks to joke that was Let’s Go Pikachu and Eevee, I’ve lost a lot of interest in this franchise, you find that they really don’t make a big effort to impress anymore, they just repack the same experience until people gets tired ot it I guess.

That’s what happens with this game, if they don’t show anything different, I think I’ll pass.

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.
